  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Numbers 18:8-9",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Numbers 18:8-9",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Having pointed out to him the duties of his function, now follows a detail of the emoluments annexed to it; which emoluments are expressly declared to be for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Aaron and his sons — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That is, for the high- priest, who undoubtedly had a principal portion, and for the inferior priests. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "I also have given thee the charge — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "I have bestowed them upon thee for thine use, with a charge that none have them but thyself. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "By reason of the anointing — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Because thou art anointed with the sacred oil, and thereby consecrated to the office of priest, see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 8:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Most holy things — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Such as were to be eaten only by the priests, and that in the sanctuary. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Reserved from the fire ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— That is, such sacrifices, or parts of sacrifices, as were not burned in the fire. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Which they shall render unto me — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "By way of compensation for a trespass committed against me, in which case a ram was to be offered, which was a most holy thing, and may be particularly designed here.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "18:8-19 All believers are spiritual priests, and God has promised to take care of them. Godliness has the promise of the life that now is. And from the provision here made for the priests, the apostle shows that it is the duty of christian churches to maintain their ministers. Scandalous maintenance makes scandalous ministers. The priests were to be wholly devoted to their ministry, not diverted from it, or disturbed in it, by worldly care or business. Also, that they might be examples of living by faith, not only in God's providence, but in his ordinances. The best should be offered for the first-fruits unto the Lord. Those who think to save, by putting God off with the refuse, deceive themselves, for God is not mocked.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
