  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". A general statement that all the holy things of Israel are the property of the priests. This is afterwards limited by the regulations in the following verses.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the charge of",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "my contributions",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] i.e. the contributions made to me. See on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 18:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". If ‘the charge’ (the ordinary rendering of the Heb. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "mishmereth",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") is correct, the expression must mean ‘the duty of taking care that the contributions are not profaned through being eaten by non-priestly persons.’ But it is better to render ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "that which is kept",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "of my contributions",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", i.e. that portion of the sacrifice which is not burnt, but reserved to be eaten. This concrete force of the word ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "mishmereth",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is unique, but not impossible.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "by reason of the anointing",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The marg. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "for a portion",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is correct. In ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 7:35",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " a word from the same root is rendered ‘anointing-portion,’ but it is doubtful if it has any connexion with the root ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "mâshaḥ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " which signifies ‘anoint.’",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "8–20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The priests’ dues",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". These are as follows: (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "a",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") All meal-, sin-, and guilt-offerings, with the exception of those parts which are burnt on the altar, i.e. given to God. These may be eaten by any ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "male",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " member of the priestly families ‘in a very holy place’ (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Numbers 18:9-10",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Numbers 18:9-10",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "b",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") Those portions of a ‘gift’ (i.e. a peace-offering) which are not eaten by the worshipper himself, nor given to God by being burnt on the altar; the priests’ portions thus consisted of the ‘contribution,’ including that part of it called the ‘wave-offering.’ These may be eaten by any member, male ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "or female",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", of the priestly families, who is free from ceremonial pollution (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Numbers 18:11",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Numbers 18:11",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The fact that females might eat it implies that it might be eaten anywhere outside the sacred precincts, into which no female was admitted, (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "c",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") All the best of the fresh oil, wine, and corn (further defined as ‘the first’ of them), and the first-ripe fruits. These may be eaten by the same persons as in (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "b",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Numbers 18:12-13",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Numbers 18:12-13",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "d",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") Every ‘devoted’ thing (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Numbers 18:14",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Numbers 18:14",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "e",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") The first-born of all clean cattle (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Numbers 18:15",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Numbers 18:15",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " a), with the exception of the blood and fat which were given to God (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Numbers 18:17",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
